JOHANNESBURG - Former South African Sports Confederation and Olympic Committee (Sascoc) CEO, Tubby Reddy, who has vowed to fight his sacking to the death, says he has nothing to lose. He has threatened to spill the beans on the shenanigans that have engulfed the Olympic body under his watch. READ: Stoke City sack Hughes after cup exit Sascoc fired Reddy, Jean Kelly, and CFO Vinesh Maharaj earlier this month following lengthy investigations. Among other things, Reddy was accused of colluding with an agent of a Chinese sportswear brand by inflating prices of kit for South Africa’s Olympic team, as well as sexual harassment. eNCA sports reporter, OG Molefe has more on the story in the video gallery above. eNCA